 In the matter between DAILY MAVERICK                                                                                               APPLICANT AND OUPA SEGALWE                                                                                           RESPONDENT MATTER NO: 4316/03/2019 CORRECTIVE DECISION ON AN APPLICATION FOR LEAVE TO APPEAL (a)     leave to appeal is granted to the applicant only on whether or not the applicant has transgressed any clause of the Code; and (b)     no leave is granted on whether or not the respondent’s reply, which must comply with the guidelines set out in the Ombud’s Ruling of 11 December 2019, should be published. Dated this 13th day of March 2020 Judge B M Ngoepe, Chair, Appeals Panel 